AI-SHA-Production — NOTICE / Attribution
========================================

This repository is a consolidated ("best-of-three") merge of three AI-SHA
sources into a single full-robot ROS 2 workspace. It is distributed under the
MIT License (see LICENSE), inherited from the Ahmed28309/AI-SHA project from
which the robotics/hardware packages originate.

Provenance of merged content
----------------------------
* Brain, perception & production packaging
  (src/aisha_brain, src/llm_node, src/stt_node, src/yolov8_ros, ADRs, build_ros.sh):
  from hsdaou/AI-SHA-Production.

* Hardware, drivers, sensors, motor/encoder odometry + EKF fusion, Arduino/Pi
  firmware, the farm brain (src/robot_brain), plant-disease training, and docs/:
  from Ahmed28309/AI-SHA — a high-school robotics team project. Contributors
  include (per that repository's git history): SrinjayUbuntu, Ahmed28309, hsdaou,
  srinjaycode, Noureldin-Puterisms265, Srinjay-JavaScript, dynamicskeleton,
  pixelsauras, jameelon8-web, Yasir-guburi. Refer to that repository for the
  authoritative authorship and commit history.

* Nav2 navigation stack (src/robot_bringup/config/nav2_params.yaml) and the
  src/aisha_integration meta-package: from the local "AI-SHA Reimagined" tree.

This merge preserves the upstream MIT license. It does not attempt to rewrite or
re-attribute individual commit authorship; consult each source repository for
full history. See MERGE_NOTES.md for per-package decisions.
